CLASS:: NoLagControlSpec
summary:: datatype specifying a 'control' rate input that does not any lag applied to it
categories:: Spec, Libraries>crucial>Spec
related:: Classes/ControlSpec

DESCRIPTION:: Control rate inputs are usually given a Lag to smooth out any zipper noises.  Some inputs like those used for binary flags (eg 0/1 to toggle playing) should not ever get a lag.



